researching the library more i realized a few things that are kinda dealbreakers without some *cursed* designs:
- adding headings wraps an svg and header elements *inside* of a figure element, which means i can't directly write it to an .svg file
- puppeteer can only output elements to a raster image or a pdf
- therefore the only way i could get to vector is to first go through pdf, which means... chart -> DOM element -> HTML -> PDF -> SVG [the pain is awfulll]

a bonus is that the output file is *very* strongly typed (which is a good thing), so i tried reformatting the string by removing the file extension and adding it back, which could have worked but the syntax didn't end up being correct and i found out you could use `as` to make things simpler. anyways witness this beautiful typescript code:
